SIMPLE: spawn
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Spawn
<hw>Spawn</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Spawned</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Spawning</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[OE. <ets>spanen</ets>, OF.
<ets>espandre</ets>, properly, to shed, spread, L. <ets>expandere</ets>
to spread out. See <er>Expand</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To produce
or deposit (eggs), as fishes or frogs do.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To bring forth; to generate; -- used in
contempt.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>One edition [of books] <qex>spawneth</qex> another.</q>
<rj><qau>Fuller.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Spawn</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Spawn
<hw>Spawn</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To deposit eggs, as
fish or frogs do.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To issue, as offspring; -- used
contemptuously.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Spawn</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Spawn
<hw>Spawn</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[⟦root⟧170. See <er>Spawn</er>,
<pos>v. t.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The ova, or eggs, of fishes,
oysters, and other aquatic animals.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Any product or offspring; -- used
contemptuously.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Hort.)</fld> <def>The buds or branches produced
from underground stems.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>The white fibrous matter forming
the matrix from which fungi.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Spawn eater</b></col> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>a small
American cyprinoid fish (<spn>Notropis Hudsonius</spn>) allied to the
dace.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Spawner</ent>⟦br⟧
